"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The issue with the code is that it tries to plot datetime objects directly on the x-axis. Matplotlib requires numerical values for plotting, not datetime objects. Also, when adding text to the plot using plt.text(), the x-coordinate should be a numerical value, not a string representing a date.\",\n  \"patch\": \"15c15\\n< ax.plot(df['C'], df['E'])\\n---\\n> ax.plot_date(df['C'], df['E'])\\n\\n17c17\\n< plt.text(\\\"2013-01-05\\\", 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\\n---\\n> plt.text(pd.to_datetime(\\\"2013-01-05\\\").toordinal(), 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\"\n}"